what security does the firewall project offer stanford answers stanford university stanford answers what security does the firewall project offer categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home what security does the firewall project offer search this site a firewall examines source and destination information and then either permits or denies access to hosts and application ports for example a firewall can restrict access to your windows servers from the internet although firewalls provide a level of security against unwanted traffic they are only part of the overall security of the stanford network it is crucial that you keep your computer's anti virus software current and that you secure your password computer and data see the secure computing page for more information the main function of firewalls is to restrict in bound traffic to only those hosts that need it and only through very specific ports and services in doing so it helps to protect all systems located in the firewalled network because the firewall cannot protect against an infected or compromised host such as a laptop that is brought into the network patching and updating are also critical components of securing your systems in combination firewalling patching and running anti virus are the foundation for information security best practices firewalls stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
